msIdentifier.repository: Quaker and Special Collections, Rendel Harris

msContents.summary: Book 4 of 5 from a Latin theological compendium that was extremely popular among Catholics in Arabic Garshuni (Arabic in Syriac script) translation. This copy includes Part 10, on the sacraments generally and Part 11, on the sacraments individually.
msContents.textLang: Arabic Garshuni; Serto with a few notes in Arabic script

author.persName: La Poype de Vertrieu, Jean Claude de, 1655-1732

author.name: J. Rendel Harris Collection (Quaker & Special Collections, Haverford College)

supportDesc.extent: iv, 228, ii leaves : 205 x 145 (170 x 105) mm bound to 210 x 150 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto.

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard; blind-stamped central design composed of four floral motifs around a central point with lines and pendants in the four cardinal directions; cornerpieces and frame.

origin.p: Copy completed 12 September 1836 (note in Arabic in Arabic script f. 227r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by J. Rendel Harris.
